@scoder In the following:
```
X diff = (X) 0 - (X) 1;
```
I think the substraction result is a signed `int`, not a potentially unsigned `X`, due to C/C++ operator rules, so you'd need something like the, arguably cumbersome, following:
```
X diff = (X) ((X) 0 - (X) 1);
```
